article.description: — Fred Cleveland Jr. had 24 points in North Carolina Central's 78-75 overtime win against Campbell on Monday night.
article.headline: Cleveland scores 24, leads North Carolina Central past Campbell 78-75 in OT
article.linkText: Cleveland scores 24, leads North Carolina Central past Campbell 78-75 in OT
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. -- — Fred Cleveland Jr. had 24 points in North Carolina Central's 78-75 overtime win against Campbell on Monday night. Cleveland added six assists for the Eagles (3-3). Po'Boigh King scored 15 points and added nine rebounds. Ja'Darius Harris had 13 points and was 6 of 15 shooting (0 for 5 from 3-point range). Anthony Dell'Orso led the way for the Fighting Camels (1-3) with 25 points. Tasos Cook added 10 points and two steals for Campbell. Mason Grant also recorded 10 points and three blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
